name: Banana
description: A banana is an elongated, edible fruit – botanically a berry – produced by several kinds of large herbaceous flowering plants in the genus Musa. In some countries, bananas used for cooking may be called "plantains", distinguishing them from dessert bananas.

name: Crab Pool Security
description: In Crab Pool hermit crabs armed with pool cues hit snail shells in an attempt to deshell their opponent. Snail shells propelled by the cue have a green trail indicating they are powerful enough to knock the shell off a crab so be careful! Controls: analogue sticks to move and aim, R1 to shoot with pool cue, L1 to block by hiding in shell.

name: Guava
description: Guava is a common tropical fruit cultivated in many tropical and subtropical regions. Psidium guajava is a small tree in the myrtle family, native to Mexico, Central America, the Caribbean and northern South America.
